features: Facial Tissues Boxes - Each handy box contains 56 luxuriously soft bamboo facial tissues. Bamboo tissues are naturally softer and stronger than regular paper tissues.
Facial Tissues Cube - Packaged in convenient cube boxes with an easy to open dispenser on top. Making these the perfect choice for both at home and car tissues.

Kind To You and The Planet - Our facial tissues are made from sustainably sourced bamboo from FSC certified forests. By using bamboo tissue instead of traditional paper, we can put a stop to deforestation of our rainforest.
100% Plastic Free - At The Cheeky Panda, we are committed to reducing waste around the planet. That's why you'll find our tissue box and tissues contain zero traces of plastic anywhere,

Vegan and Cruelty-Free - We make our natural sustainable products based on the standards set by the Vegan Society. None of our ingredients and formulations were tried on animals anywhere in the world.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: The Cheeky Panda team It's Panda Friendly - don't worry. All Panda food is safe! Since our creation in 2016, we use FSC certified bamboo with NEPCon The bamboo we use is not the same species of bamboo that pandas eat Why do we use Bamboo? Because it is Ultra-Sustainable and Skin Friendly! Bamboo is the fastest growing plant in the world, growing up to 1 meter a day! As bamboo is a grass, it does not require re-planting after harvest Bamboo is naturally hypoallergenic and kind to skin Bamboo fibre is super soft and absorbent The long fibre in bamboo contains less dust particles

We're a young & dynamic company making Ultra-Sustainable 100% Bamboo Tissue & Wipes. We aim to inspire positive change for our future through innovative products. All of The Cheeky Panda products are 100% virgin bamboo, which has only been treated with hydrogen peroxide for the whitening process. No other de-inking chemicals, unlike those used in recycled papers. Bearing in mind the usual caveats that everyone is different, they are naturally hypoallergenic. In 2019, we became the first tissue company in the UK to be Vegan Registered with The Vegan Society. In 2019, we also became Leaping Bunny Certified with Cruelty Free International, meaning we do zero animal testing in our process! Since 2016, we have been Carbon Balanced, protecting plants and animals in endangered rainforests through our partnership with The World Land Trust and NEPCon.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good but overpriced
reviews.reviewText: These are strong and don't tear easily. They keep your hands clean and absorb what they need to. However they are not soft which is a deal-breaker for some people. I can live with that if they don't melt on use, but I really hate that these are bleached white and they are overpriced. I will find an unbleached, cheaper alternative that's hopefully softer too.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 29, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best for the environment
reviews.reviewText: Everything about these is environmentally friendly. The box they are stored in, the box they are shipped in, the tissues themselves are made of bamboo which a renewable resource as it regrows itself and doesn’t have to be planted as a seed every time one is removed. The tissues are thick and absorbent. They are not quite as soft as the softest Kleenex or Puffs that are advertised for raw noses but they’re not rough either. If you truly care about the environment give these a try at least once.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars they help the planet
reviews.reviewText: I bought these to save trees and they do that!!! They are not very soft and doesn't absorb great, however they hold up better than most so you can use them over and over. Defiantly a planet saver.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 26, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I love bamboo TP and paper towels and love that they are compostable. BUT... the facial tissues are far too rough around tender eye skin and rough on the nose, so I have to stick with aloe-infused Kleenex.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 20, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I always bring back tissue packs from Italy because although rough, they are thicker than American tissue, and do not break down into a pile of lint. I don't mind texture so much (and I have allergies), because one tissue goes a long way. This is what I was hoping for when I ordered the bamboo tissue. It does come close - softer, but not as thick as the Italian ones, I went through the box pretty quickly. So given that, it is WAY too expensive!! I also tried cotton tissues, also hypoallergenic and lint-free. The cotton is softer then the bamboo and not quite as costly.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars No fragrance and almost zero lint
reviews.reviewText: I got really sick of linty tissues that were somehow full of fragrances even though they said they were unscented (an issue I ran into with both puffs and kleenex). A face full of perfume and dust is the last thing I need when I’m already sneezing or my eyes are watering.So I went on a quest to find a better tissue, and that quest ended with these. They have almost no lint and absolutely zero fragrance.They also hold up better than normal tissues when damp, so they’re great for blotting excess facial serums and oils if I get a bit overzealous.The only issue I’ve run into is that the company twice sent the wrong shaped box. I didn’t have the heart to send them back (the tissues inside are the same, after all). Haven’t had and problems with that for a while, so hopefully they’ve gotten that problem sorted.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best Ever & they don't make me cough
reviews.reviewText: This tissue is amazing. I noticed that I don't start coughing after I use them, which always happened to me when I used kleenex and other brands. After learning about the chemical process used in regular tissues from trees, I was horrified. So that's what must have caused coughing. But I won't use any other type of tissues, except bamboo. Plus it helps to save our environment and our precious trees that take years/decades to grow.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Excellent company and good try, just rough texture
reviews.reviewText: I was happy to pay the extra for this box of tissue from this company because the bamboo is certified as being from well-managed forests, they donate part to protect rainforests, their packaging is fully recyclable, and they are certified as following high standards of social and environmental impact.Also their bamboo is hypoallergenic has less tissue dust and there's no fertilizer de-inking agents BPA or added fragrance, which all sounded wonderful.The problem was that the tissue was really lacked flexibility. Although it had a smooth texture, it felt hard and scratchy against my nose, and now I've got a little abrasions because of it.If they could make them less rigid, it would be a welcome improvement.Possibly, make them in 2-ply instead of 3-ply would help. Removing that 3rd layer will make them less thick, more flexible, and possibly feel softer on the nose.
